First Lady Michelle Obama will be delivering commencement addresses at Eastern Kentucky University, Bowie State University, and the Martin Luther King, Jr. Academic Magnet High School for Health Sciences and Engineering. She will be speaking at Eastern Kentucky University as part of her Joining Forces initiative to support veterans and military families. The university has received national recognition for its commitment to helping veterans further their education. She will be speaking at Bowie State University, which is Maryland's oldest historically black university, and at the Martin Luther King Academic Magnet High School for Health Sciences and Engineering, which is consistently ranked among the best public schools in the nation for its academic rigor and high graduation rate. These commencement addresses are open press, but space is limited. Media members who wish to cover the commencements must RSVP directly to the schools. In the past, Mrs. Obama has delivered commencement addresses at various universities and schools across the country.